      • clear

        void clear()
        Clear the transformed model and all other intermediate BDD information. Should be called when the transformation is not needed anymore. Does not clear the original model.

      • projectToOriginalModel

        StateValues projectToOriginalModel(StateValues svTransformedModel)
                            throws PrismException
        Take a StateValues object for the transformed model and project the values to the original model.
        The svTransformedModel argument is consumed/cleared and should not be used afterwards.
        Parameters:
        svTransformedModel - a StateValues object for the transformed model
        Returns:
        a corresponding StateValues object for the original model.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getTransformedStatesOfInterest

        JDDNode getTransformedStatesOfInterest()
        Get the transformed state set of the states of interest, i.e., the set of states that should be calculated to allow a successful application of the projectToOriginalModel method.
